01:07:09.250 --> 01:07:13.090
doing this on American hagwons,
because I clearly remember--

01:07:13.090 --> 01:07:16.540
I was teaching fourth grade--
a girl comes into my class,

01:07:16.540 --> 01:07:17.950
and she's crying.

01:07:17.950 --> 01:07:19.810
And I stop her
before she enters.

01:07:19.810 --> 01:07:21.449
I'm just like, what's wrong?

01:07:21.449 --> 01:07:22.240
Why are you crying?

01:07:22.240 --> 01:07:25.480
And she said, I got
a 90 on my test.

01:07:25.480 --> 01:07:28.342
And I was like, OK, well,
you know, are you OK?

01:07:28.342 --> 01:07:29.800
Are you worried
about your parents?

01:07:29.800 --> 01:07:31.633
Are you worried about
your homeroom teacher?

01:07:31.633 --> 01:07:34.450
And she goes, no, I'm worried
about what my hagwon teacher is

01:07:34.450 --> 01:07:35.220
going to say.

01:07:35.220 --> 01:07:37.240
And I'm worried about
the consequences

01:07:37.240 --> 01:07:38.890
of getting a 90 on my test.

01:07:38.890 --> 01:07:41.230
And I think seeing
the prevalence

01:07:41.230 --> 01:07:44.350
of the hagwon culture, not
only in America, where--

01:07:44.350 --> 01:07:45.670
I grew up in Queens as well--

01:07:45.670 --> 01:07:50.350
but in Korea, I think
it's a powerful thing

01:07:50.350 --> 01:07:54.280
to create understanding
of why hagwons exist,

01:07:54.280 --> 01:07:56.530
and why it's so important,
and why it's so prevalent.

01:07:56.530 --> 01:08:00.190
But I'm wondering how do you
balance between understanding

01:08:00.190 --> 01:08:03.580
the darkness and the
unintended consequences

01:08:03.580 --> 01:08:06.490
and the negative impact
it has on these kids,

01:08:06.490 --> 01:08:11.020
particularly because the
suicide rate is so high?

01:08:11.020 --> 01:08:15.280
I'm wondering, how have you
seen in your research push

01:08:15.280 --> 01:08:18.490
for change, a push for
change to stay away

01:08:18.490 --> 01:08:21.700
and to strive away
from the hagwons,

01:08:21.700 --> 01:08:25.060
while building
understanding of why that

01:08:25.060 --> 01:08:28.010
exists in the Korean culture?

